meta {
  name: POST /api/chat/:patientId — turn 3: provoke the tool-use loop
  type: http
  seq: 3
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/api/chat/margaret-chen
  body: json
  auth: none
}

body:json {
  {
    "message": "Pull the GC-IPL trend across all of her OCTs and compare the most recent scan with the one before it. Is it getting worse?",
    "conversation_id": "{{conversationId}}"
  }
}

tests {
  test("stream opens with 200 and SSE content type", function() {
    expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(200);
    expect(String(res.getHeader('content-type'))).to.contain('text/event-stream');
  });

  test("the model invoked tools and the done event lists them", function() {
    const raw = typeof res.getBody() === 'string' ? res.getBody() : JSON.stringify(res.getBody());
    expect(raw, 'tool_use events should stream live').to.contain('"type":"tool_use"');
    const doneLine = raw.split('\n').filter(function(line) { return line.indexOf('"type":"done"') !== -1; }).pop();
    expect(doneLine, 'terminal done event').to.be.a('string');
    const done = JSON.parse(doneLine.replace(/^data:\s*/, ''));
    expect(done.tools_used).to.be.an('array');
    expect(done.tools_used.length, 'tools_used must not be empty for this ask').to.be.greaterThan(0);
  });
}

docs {
  # Turn 3: tool invocation, visible in the stream

  **What it proves:** the agent *invokes tools to retrieve and reason
  over patient data* (the rubric's words). Measurement trends live in the
  stored image analyses — NOT in the source documents attached to the
  prompt — so answering this ask honestly forces the model through its
  read-only, patient-scoped toolset (`get_measurement_trend`, usually
  followed by `compare_scans`).

  **What to look for in the stream:**

  ```
  data: {"type":"tool_use","name":"get_measurement_trend","input":{"metric":"GC-IPL"}}

  data: {"type":"tool_result","name":"get_measurement_trend","ok":true}

  data: {"type":"tool_use","name":"compare_scans","input":{...}}

  data: {"type":"tool_result","name":"compare_scans","ok":true}

  data: {"type":"delta","text":"GC-IPL has thinned from 82 to 70 µm ..."}

  data: {"type":"done","conversation_id":"...","tools_used":["get_measurement_trend","compare_scans"],...}
  ```

  Every tool is Zod-contracted in and out, executes over THIS patient's
  bundle only (a foreign patient's ids structurally error), and a failing
  tool returns a structured `{error}` the model recovers from — the loop
  is capped at 4 rounds before a final, tool-free answer is forced.

  **Determinism note:** which tools the live model picks is model
  behavior, not machinery — the deterministic guarantees (threading,
  verbatim tool_result plumbing, denial, round cap, error recovery) are
  locked by the `multi-turn-conversation` eval suite; this request shows
  the same loop working end-to-end against the deployed stack.
}
